fontdisplay is a simple X11 program that renders the alphabet,
numbers and symbols with the specified font.
For more information about it's usage check `man fontdisplay`.

This program requires libxcb, libxcb-image, libfreetype2 and
libfontconfig to be installed.
In order to build this program you need to run `make`.

